<exercise checkit-seed="0002" checkit-slug="AI2" checkit-title="Arc Length">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Consider the curve <m>y=3 \, x^{2} + 4 \, x</m> defined on <m>[2, 4]</m>.
            <ol>
                <li>
                    Estimate the arclength of this curve with <m>4</m> line segments with <m>\Delta x = 0.5</m>.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Find an integral that computes the arclength of this curve.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <me>
               \begin{array}{|c|c|c|c|c|}
              \hline
              x_i
              &amp;
              x_{i+1}
              &amp;
              f(x_{i})
              &amp;
              f(x_{i+1})
              &amp;
              \text{Length of segment}          
              \\
              \hline
               2
              &amp; 
               2.5
              &amp;
               20.0
              &amp; 
               28.75
              &amp;
               8.7643         
                  \\
               2.5
              &amp; 
               3.0
              &amp;
               28.75
              &amp; 
               39.0
              &amp;
               10.2622         
                  \\
               3.0
              &amp; 
               3.5
              &amp;
               39.0
              &amp; 
               50.75
              &amp;
               11.7606         
                  \\
               3.5
              &amp; 
               4.0
              &amp;
               50.75
              &amp; 
               64.0
              &amp;
               13.2594         
                  \\
              
              \hline
              \end{array}
          </me>
              The estimated length of this curve is 44.046499999999995.      
                </li>
                <li>
                    The arclength is computed via <me>\int_{ 2 }^{ 4 }\sqrt{1+ \left(6 \, x + 4\right)^2}dx.</me> 
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
